'''''Medical World News''''' was an American magazine for the medical profession. It was published between 1960 and 1994.
==History and profile== ''Medical World News'' was founded in April 1960<ref>{{cite web|title=Guide to the Morris Fishbein Papers 1912-1976|url=https://www.lib.uchicago.edu/e/scrc/findingaids/view.php?eadid=ICU.SPCL.FISHBEIN&q=Illinois%20-%20Politics%20and%20Government|publisher=The University of Chicago Library|accessdate=July 30, 2015}}</ref> by [[Maxwell M Geffen]], a New York publisher. The founding editor of ''Medical World News'' was [[Morris Fishbein]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Where have you gone, Morris Fishbein? Our nation turns its lonely eyes to you|url=http://disruptedphysician.com/2015/04/22/where-have-you-gone-morris-fishbein-our-nation-turns-its-lonely-eyes-to-you/|accessdate=July 30, 2015|work=Disrupted Physician|date=April 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=William H. Taft|title=Encyclopedia of Twentieth Century Journalists|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6-csCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT208|accessdate=July 30, 2015|date=July 16, 2015|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-317-40324-1|page=208}}</ref> The magazine was later sold to [[McGraw-Hill]]<ref>{{cite book|title=New Scientist|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pCkprha8oIAC&pg=PA598|accessdate=October 16, 2016|date=November 21, 1974|publisher=Reed Business Information|page=598|issn=0262-4079}}</ref> and in March 1981 it was sold by McGraw-Hill to Hospital Equities,<ref>{{cite news|author1=Philip H. Dougherty|title=Medical World News Sold by McGraw-Hill|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1981/03/03/business/advertising-medical-world-news-sold-by-mcgraw-hill.html|accessdate=October 15, 2016|work=The New York Times|date=March 3, 1981}}</ref> an operator of health care facilities. [[Miller Freeman, Inc.|Miller Freeman]] acquired the magazine from Hospital Equities.<ref>{{cite news|title=J. Russell Denson Named President and Chief Executive Officer of Gruner + Jahr USA|url=http://www.guj.de/en/press/press-releases/j-russell-denson-named-president-and-chief-executive-officer-of-gruner-jahr-usa/|accessdate=November 29, 2015|work=Gruner and Jahr|date=May 26, 2004|location=Hamburg}}</ref> In 1994 the magazine ceased publication.
In 1985 McGovern Center for Historical Collections (endowed by [[John P. McGovern]]) acquired an archive of [[photograph]]s from ''Medical World News''. This archive is accessible at [[The Texas Medical Center Library]] in [[Houston]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Medical World News Photograph Collection|url=http://library.tmc.edu/mcgovern/conducting-research/finding-aids/mwn-ic077/|work=McGovern Historical Center|accessdate=February 7, 2017}}</ref>
