'''Rolande Kammogne''' (born May 31, 1982) is a Cameroonian entrepreneur and television producer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.camernews.com/medias-plus-de-10-millions-de-personnes-ont-regarde-voice-afrique-francophone-au-cameroun-selon-rolande-kammogne-la-vice-presidente-de-vox-africa/ |title=Médias: Plus de 10 millions de personnes ont regardé «The Voice Afrique francophone» au Cameroun, selon Rolande Kammogne, la vice-présidente de Vox Africa |website=camernews.com |publisher=Camernews |access-date=2018-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218141036/http://www.camernews.com/medias-plus-de-10-millions-de-personnes-ont-regarde-voice-afrique-francophone-au-cameroun-selon-rolande-kammogne-la-vice-presidente-de-vox-africa/ |archive-date=2017-02-18 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://fr.news.yahoo.com/au-cameroun-rolande-kammogne-donne-095053282.html |title=Au Cameroun, Rolande Kammogne donne de la voix à l'Afrique |website=fr.news.yahoo.com |publisher=[[Yahoo News]], France}}</ref> She is the founder of the [[Pan-Africanism|pan-African]] [[Television channel|TV channel]] VoxAfrica.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lesdirigeantes.com/rolande-kammogne-directrice-et-fondatrice-de-vox-africa/|title=Rolande Kammogne Directrice et Fondatrice de Vox Africa|date=2016-12-13|work=Les Dirigeantes|access-date=2018-08-18|language=fr-FR|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731162623/http://www.lesdirigeantes.com/rolande-kammogne-directrice-et-fondatrice-de-vox-africa/|archive-date=2017-07-31|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>
== Early life == Rolande is the daughter of {{ill|Paul Fokam|fr}}, a Cameroonian entrepreneur. She was born on May 31, 1982.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://abidjan.net/qui/profil.asp?id=963|title=RolandeKAMMOGNE (Directrice fondatrice de la chaine panafricaine VoxAfrica) - Abidjan.net Qui est Qui|last=coast|first=Weblogy, Abidjan, Côte d'Ivoire, cote d'ivoire, Ivory|work=Abidjan.net|access-date=2018-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171015030208/http://abidjan.net/qui/profil.asp?id=963|archive-date=2017-10-15|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> In 2004, she graduated with a degree in mathematics, statistics and management systems from [[Columbia University School of General Studies|Columbia University]] in the United States. She wrote a thesis on the need for the creation of a media that would connect all the black diasporas of the world.<ref name=":0" /> Upon leaving school, she accepted an internship at [[Killer Films]] where she worked alongside [[Christine Vachon]].
== Career == In 2006, with a team of analysts, she prepared the business plan for the creation of a pan-African television. In September 2007, she moved to [[London]] to realize the project.
=== VoxAfrica === In January 2008, the first pan-African, bilingual and independent television channel, VoxAfrica took its first steps on the Internet at the [[Africa Cup of Nations|African Nations Cup]] in Ghana. In May 2008, the channel emits its first signal now visible in Africa via satellite.<ref name=":0" />
