'''Salma Ali Saif Bin Hareb''' is an Emirati business executive. From 2005 to 2015 she was chief executive officer of [[Jebel Ali Free Zone]] and of Economic Zones World, the parent company of Jebel Ali Free Zone.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=22909930&privcapId=52511612 Salma Ali Saif Saeed Bin Hareb: Executive Profile & Biography]</ref> She is the first woman in the [[Middle East and North Africa]] to be appointed head of an [[economic free zone]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = 100 Most Powerful Arab Women 2011|url = http://www.arabianbusiness.com/100-most-powerful-arab-women-2011-384182.html?view=profile&itemid=383757|website = Arabian Business|accessdate = 2015-10-20}}</ref>

In 2014, Forbes ranked her as the third most powerful Arab woman.<ref name="Forbes">[https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/en/list/200-most-powerful-arab-women-2014-executive-management/item/3/ 200 Most Powerful Arab Women – 2014: #3 Salma Ali Saif Bin Hareb]</ref>


